        <num>CCRP 385</num>
        <heading>385.  Affidavit</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 385.  Affidavit
An affidavit is a written accusation of crime made under oath and signed by the affiant.  It must be filed in open court in a court having jurisdiction to try the offense, or in the office of the clerk thereof.</p>
        </content>
